node.text:
Training squad in Kenya… Go, go, go! 🔛  Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory)

Isn't this inspiring? Tag your running squad! (📹: @timkalkkuhl)

node.text:
by @tri_from_nobody 💪 We can post your photos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures.

42km running

Special thanks to @minghan_lee for photographing
and supplements

Shout to my dad (62-year old)who kept company with me for the last 21km!

You’re never too old! 💪 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our page, use the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

I love to get help in this when I can, so when Andrew is around he comes and adjust me.

And……🏄🏻‍♀️
I took the opportunity to try out the paddle board for a Bhekasana 😜
The hard part was to come from Urdhva mukha svanasana to down dog 😂

So many good benefits;
In Bhekasana, the navel is pressed on the floor, as in Salabhasana A & B.
The benefits of these postures are similar:
* Stretch the thighs and hips
* Release tension from the knees and hips
* Cleanse manipura-cakra
.
📽 @lottasebzdayoga

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Running | Runners | Run on September 12, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, road and text that says 'If I see you running, I don't care if you're big, slow, fast, out of shape, in shape, obese or skinny. If you're running, I'm rooting for you.'.

node.text:
Running has taught me 💪 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process.

(📷: @variations.ofheather)

NEXEL LEVEL LEGS😳🔥 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos/videos in our account: @RunningTerritory

Save it for later!

The best way to overcome a “plateau” is by switching up your routine to keep your body guessing what’s next. The human body adapts to stress, this means as you get stronger your training also needs to increase in difficulty. Keep it fun & challenging 👊🏽

METHOD ➡️ 12-15 reps per side | 4 sets | 30 secs rest

Tag your friends & go crush it! ⤵️

📽 @realrubaali
